  "title": "Warehouse Executive/Production Support (Energy & Power Industry) - S$3,500 basic + AWS + VB",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Production Support / Warehouse Executive</strong></h2><p><strong>Location:</strong> Pioneer<br /><strong>Salary:</strong> Up to $3,500<br /><strong>Benefits:</strong> AWS + Variable Bonus (VB)<br /><strong>Flexible Benefits:</strong> $500 per year<br /><strong>Shift Work:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Day Shift: 7:30am – 5:00pm</p></li><li><p>Night Shift: 7:30pm – 5:00am<br /><em>(Rotation every 2 weeks)</em></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Summary</strong></h3><p>Support day-to-day materials and parts flow, movement, and storage. Responsible for receiving, packaging, storing, and transporting materials and parts within the site, including handling of bulky items using forklift operations.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Receive and issue stocks in accordance with relevant shipping documents.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate stock records and inventory documentation.</p></li><li><p>Load and unload incoming and outgoing goods using forklift.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal requestors and suppliers on stock arrivals.</p></li><li><p>Participate in the company’s annual stock take as assigned.</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper 5S housekeeping practices and stock security.</p></li><li><p>Receive and dispatch materials/parts to the correct departments.</p></li><li><p>Perform tasks in accordance with standard operating procedures, specifications, and quality documentation.</p></li><li><p>Communicate parts status with cross-functional teams to meet production needs.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with all EHS (Environment, Health & Safety) procedures and requirements.</p></li><li><p>Complete all material movement and hand-off documentation neatly, accurately, and legibly.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Prior experience in a warehouse or logistics operations environment is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Able to perform rotating shift work.</p></li><li><p>Valid Forklift experience/certification</p></li></ul>",
